summary:
Let me use a simpler sed command to fix this:

<tool_call>
<function=Bash>
<parameter=command>
sed -i '/getClientIp(req/,/return req.socket.remoteAddress/{
    /const forwarded = req.headers\[.x-forwarded-for.\];/,/return req.socket.remoteAddress/c\
    // SECURITY FIX: Do not trust X-Forwarded-For header for rate limiting\
    // as it can be spoofed by attackers to bypass rate limits\
    return req.socket.remoteAddress || '\''127.0.0.1'\'';
}' app/ratelimiter.ts
</parameter>
</function>
</tool_call>
